{"abstract": "Chrysler will recall more than 228,000 vehicles because their airbags could unexpectedly inflate without a crash.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/03/business/jeep-cherokees-to-be-recalled-to-upgrade-airbag-software.html", "snippet": "Chrysler will recall more than 228,000 vehicles because their airbags could unexpectedly inflate without a crash.", "lead_paragraph": "Chrysler will recall more than 228,000 vehicles because their airbags could unexpectedly inflate without a crash. The company will upgrade software governing side-curtain and seat-mounted side airbags in Jeep Cherokees from the 2014-15 model years, including more than 168,000 vehicles in the United States. Chrysler engineers initiated an investigation after getting reports of \u201ca small number of inadvertent deployments involving drivers who executed extreme maneuvers.\u201d In these cases, the airbag systems, sensing potential rollovers, automatically activated. The action follows a much larger recall for inadvertent airbag deployments announced on Saturday by regulators at the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration. That recall covers about 2.1 million vehicles made by Chrysler, Toyota and Honda with airbags that might suddenly deploy. On Tuesday, it will release trade figures for August; exports have been flat so far this year, and imports declined 15 percent in the first seven months of 2015. Other reports include inflation figures on Wednesday and industrial output, investment and retail sales on Saturday. Investors will also be watching on Monday for August data on China\u2019s foreign exchange reserves. While still the world\u2019s largest, China\u2019s reserves are expected to have declined after the surprise devaluation last month of its currency, the renminbi, which has raised concerns over {"abstract": "Toyota is recalling 198,000 more vehicles because the airbag inflater produced by Takata could rupture.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/03/business/toyota-recalls-almost-200000-vehicles-with-takata-airbags.html", "snippet": "Toyota is recalling 198,000 more vehicles because the airbag inflater produced by Takata could rupture.", "lead_paragraph": "Toyota is recalling 331,000 more vehicles worldwide because the airbag inflater produced by Takata could rupture, sending metal shards into the passenger compartment, the automaker said on Wednesday. The new action covers the passenger-side airbag on the 2008 Corolla and Corolla Matrix as well as the 2008-10 Lexus SC 430. The company said it was not aware of any injuries associated with the new recall. In June, the automaker recalled earlier model years of those vehicles as part of an action covering almost 1.4 million vehicles. Toyota has now recalled about 15 million vehicles worldwide because of the Takata defect. Over all, 14 automakers have recalled about 24 million vehicles for the inflaters, which have been linked to 10 deaths and more than 100 injuries.", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "2", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [], "headline": {"main": "Toyota Adds 331,000 Vehicles to Takata Airbag Recall", "kicker": "Business Briefing", "content_kicker": null, "print_headline": "Toyota Adds 331,000 Vehicles to Takata Airbag Recall", "name": null, "seo": null, "sub": null}, "keywords": [{"name": "subject", "value": "Automobile Safety Features and Defects", "rank": 1, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Jensen, Christopher", "rank": 2, "major": "N"}, {"name": "organizations", "value": "Takata Corp", "rank": 3, "major": "N"}, {"name": "organizations", "value": "Toyota Motor Corp", "rank": 4, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Recalls and Bans of Products", "rank": 5, "major": "N"}], "pub_date": "2016-03-03T00:37:11+0000", "document_type": "article", "news_desk": "Business", "section_name": "Business Day", "byline": {"original": "By Christopher Jensen", "person": [{"firstname": "Christopher", "middlename": null, "lastname": "Jensen", "qualifier": null, "title": null, "role": "reported", "organization": "", "rank": 1}], "organization": null}, "type_of_material": "News", "_id": "nyt://article/22bae743-add3-5d3e-a44c-000d06e92aa8", "word_count": 125, "uri": "nyt://article/22bae743-add3-5d3e-a44c-000d06e92aa8"}
